==============================================================    9547 1451
 Covariances - BNL, July, 2011: Covariances were adopted from     9547 1451
COMMARA-2.0, which were supplied by BNL. Covariances are          9547 1451
combination of the uncertainties recommended in the assessment of 9547 1451
Ref. [1] and correlation matrices produced by the WPEC Subgroup   9547 1451
26 [2] converted to the AFCI 33-energy group structure.           9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
Following the low-fidelity approach, the uncertainties in the     9547 1451
low energy region are based on experimental uncertainties of      9547 1451
thermal cross sections, uncertainties of the resonance integrals  9547 1451
and uncertainty of the scattering radius.                         9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
In the fast region the initial estimates [2] were obtained using  9547 1451
EMPIRE/KALMAN system with default parameterization roughly        9547 1451
adjusted to reproduce trends in the experimental data. The KALMAN 9547 1451
code was run with default uncertainties assigned to the key model 9547 1451
parameters to produce covariances. The assessment [2] of these    9547 1451
initial estimates was based on the visual inspection of           9547 1451
experimental data and dispersion of available evaluations. It led 9547 1451
to considerable decrease of the elastic uncertainty and the       9547 1451
inelastic uncertainty above 6 MeV, doubled fission uncertainty    9547 1451
above 6 MeV, increased capture uncertainty in the whole fast      9547 1451
neutron range and confirmed the nu-bar uncertainties.             9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
[1] V.M. Maslov, P. Oblozinsky, M. Herman, "Review and Assessment 9547 1451
of Neutron Cross Section and Nu-bar Covariances for Advanced      9547 1451
Reactor Systems," Report BNL-81884-2008-IR, Brookhaven            9547 1451
National Laboratory (2008).                                       9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
[2] D. Rochman, M. Herman, P. Oblozinsky, and S. F. Mughabghab,   9547 1451
"Preliminary Cross Section Covariances for WPEC Subgroup 26,"     9547 1451
Report BNL-77407-2007-IR, Brookhaven National Laboratory (2007).  9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
********************* DESCRIPTION / REFERENCES *******************9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
This evaluation describes products of the neutron-induced reaction9547 1451
on Am-242m, i.e., in its long-lived metastable state 5-, 48.63keV,9547 1451
for neutron incident energies up to 20 MeV. The following cross   9547 1451
sections are present in this file: (n,n'), (n,2n), (n,3n), (n,f), 9547 1451
and (n,gamma). Secondary neutrons double-differential spectra were9547 1451
also obtained. Details on the evaluation procedure are given      9547 1451
below.                                                            9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
A coupled-channels calculation was used to infer the total,       9547 1451
elastic and reaction cross sections, and direct elastic and       9547 1451
inelastic scattering cross sections and angular distributions for 9547 1451
several excited states. The deformed optical potential used was   9547 1451
developed by P.G.Young for Am-241 and Am-243 isotopes [Yo94].     9547 1451
The details are as follows:                                       9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
------------------------------------------------------------------9547 1451
Well depth (MeV)                range (MeV)    geometry (fm)      9547 1451
------------------------------------------------------------------9547 1451
VR=52.102-27.75*X-0.30*E         0<=E<=30      rR=1.25, aR=0.60   9547 1451
WD=5.3243-9.4995*X+0.45*E        0<=E<8        rD=1.24, aD=0.55   9547 1451
WD=8.9243-9.4995*X-0.046*(E-8)   8<=E<=30                         9547 1451
WV=0                             0<=E<8        rV=1.24, aV=0.55   9547 1451
WV=-1.6+0.20*E                   8<=E<=30                         9547 1451
Vso=6.2                          0<=E<=30      rso=1.01,aso=0.75  9547 1451
------------------------------------------------------------------9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
where X=(N-Z)/A characterizes the isospin dependence. The ECIS96  9547 1451
code [Ra94] was used for the present coupled-channels calculation.9547 1451
The adopted first discrete levels for Am-242 are:                 9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
  No.  Energy (MeV)   Spin, Parity                                9547 1451
 -----------------------------------                              9547 1451
  1     -0.04863       1-                                         9547 1451
  2     -0.00453       0-                                         9547 1451
  0      0.00000       5- (metastable state)                      9547 1451
  3      0.00427       3-                                         9547 1451
  4      0.02717       2-                                         9547 1451
  5      0.05037       2-                                         9547 1451
  6      0.06537       6- (meta rotational band)                  9547 1451
  7      0.09937       5-                                         9547 1451
  8      0.10127       4-                                         9547 1451
  9      0.12237       5-                                         9547 1451
 10      0.14137       7- (meta rotational band)                  9547 1451
 11      0.14897       3-                                         9547 1451
 ..      .......       ..                                         9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
Note that the energy of the metastable state is considered to be  9547 1451
artificially zero, while the true ground-state energy is set to   9547 1451
minus the energy of the metastable state. The three first states  9547 1451
of the rotational band built on top of the metastable state are   9547 1451
coupled.                                                          9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
(n,xn) and (n,gamma) cross sections, and secondary neutrons       9547 1451
spectra were obtained with the GNASH nuclear reaction code [Yo96].9547 1451
The neutron spin-dependent transmission coefficients were obtained9547 1451
from the ECIS calculation.                                        9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
The neutron-induced fission cross section was obtained by a       9547 1451
generalized least-squares fit of experimental data using the GLUCS9547 1451
code [He80]. The fission model parameters used to calculate the   9547 1451
fission cross section in the GNASH code were adjusted to best     9547 1451
reproduce the "best-fit" experimental cross section.              9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
At low incident neutron energies, the resonance parameters were   9547 1451
directly taken from the JENDL-3.3 evaluation file. The resolved   9547 1451
resonance region extends up to 43 eV, and the unresolved resonance9547 1451
region up to 27.283 keV. A smooth transition from 27.28 keV to    9547 1451
about 90 keV was established to agree with our ECIS calculation   9547 1451
of the total cross section at higher energies.                    9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
The sections MF1,MT452,455,456 and MF5,MT18 were also adopted from9547 1451
the JENDL-3.3 evaluation.                                         9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
                                                                  9547 1451
